            <abstract>The general theorems on the equilibrium states of autonomous dynamical
                systems whose right-hand side are n-th degree polynomials are proved.
                In particular, it is shown that if a system whose right-hand side are
                mutually simple polynomials has a set number of equilibrium states,
                then they are all simple. Moreover, when certain conditions  for
                the relations between the right parts of the system are met, the Poincare index
                of any equilibrium state is one less than the power of the polynomial.
                The conditions of the absence of limit cycles of a cubic system having
                special points of the «center» type are considered. Using the canonical form
                of a cubic system having the maximum number of equilibrium states,
                Poincare indices are determined, which allows us to judge their types.
                Examples are provided to support the claims made.</abstract>
